==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Slickensides
<hw>Slick"en*sides`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The smooth, striated, or partially polished surfaces of a fissure
or seam, supposed to have been produced by the sliding of one surface on
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A variety of galena found in Derbyshire,
England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slicker</ent>⟦br⟧
